      • getComparatorExpression

        public JRExpression getComparatorExpression()
        Description copied from interface: DataLevelBucket
        Returns the comparator expression.

        The result of this expression is used to sort the buckets, in ascending or descending order (given by getOrder(). If the order type is BucketOrder.NONE, no sorting will be performed and the comparator expression will be ignored.

        If no comparator expression is specified, the natural order will be used.

        If the bucket has an order by expression, the comparator will be used to compare values as produced by that expression.

        Specified by:
        getComparatorExpression in interface DataLevelBucket
        Returns:
        the comparator expression
